description: 'I am absolutely convinced that things can change,' said French Prime Minister François Bayrou on Sunday, ahead of a new round of talks with political parties. Opposition parties, however, reaffirmed their determination to bring down the government.

headline: Sylvain Amic, president of the Musée d'Orsay and the Musée de l'Orangerie, has died
description: Appointed in 2024, the curator viewed museums as places for sharing and made the circulation of artworks and access for younger generations his main priorities. He died on Sunday, August 31, at the age of 58.

headline: 'Drag Race France': Ivorian drag queen Mami Watta's comeback victory
description: The 27-year-old queen won the second victory for an Ivorian contestant, after Keiona in 2023, in the French drag show on August 28. Her success has brought hope to Côte d'Ivoire's still-marginalized LGBTQ+ community.

headline: Marcel Gauchet, historian and philosopher: 'Progressivism has locked itself into a denial of uncomfortable realities'
description: 'May '68 Thinkers Reflect On Trump Era' (2/6). The democracy specialist explains that we are witnessing a major ideological reversal after decades of depoliticization that have allowed neoliberal individualism and 'libertarian societal values' to triumph.

headline: Video: Why are young African women manufacturing Russian drones?
description: The Alabuga Special Economic Zone, in Tatarstan, Russia, has been producing drones since the start of the war in Ukraine. There, young African women have found themselves working on production lines, lured by a misleading vocational training program.
byline: Marceau Bretonnier,  Sinead McCausland and  Thomas Eydoux

description: Members of evangelical churches, a branch of Protestantism, are increasing. These believers say they are drawn by a more informal liturgy and the emphasis on community.
